# KAI — AI-Assisted Development

## What It Is

KAI is a set of AI agents that help software teams build, review, and ship code faster. It works with Azure DevOps — reading your tickets, reviewing your pull requests, and writing code when you ask it to.

There are two ways to use it:

- **Interactive** — a developer runs commands in their editor and the AI assists step by step
- **Autonomous** — the AI runs automatically when you tag a ticket or create a pull request

Both modes produce the same kind of output: analysis comments on tickets, review comments on PRs, or branches with code changes.

## What It Does

### For Developers (Interactive)

| What | How |
|------|-----|
| Understand a ticket | AI reads the ADO story, researches the codebase, lists affected files |
| Plan the work | AI generates a step-by-step implementation plan with file paths |
| Write the code | AI executes plan steps, runs tests, commits after each step |
| Review code | AI reviews your PR or someone else's — posts comments with severity levels |
| Fix review comments | AI reads reviewer feedback, applies agreed fixes, pushes and replies |
| Fix bugs | AI triages the bug, finds affected code, creates a fix branch |
| Answer questions | AI answers architecture and "how does X work?" questions from project docs |

### For Teams (Autonomous)

These agents run automatically — no developer action needed beyond adding a tag.

| Agent | Trigger | What it does |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| **PR Review** | New PR created | Reviews code, posts comments with severity levels |
| **PR Answer** | Someone comments on your PR | Researches codebase, drafts a reply |
| **DoR Check** | Tag: `KAI-DOR-AUTOMATION` | Checks if a User Story has enough detail to start |
| **DoD Check** | Tag: `KAI-DOD-AUTOMATION` | Checks if a story meets completion criteria |
| **Estimation** | Tag: `KAI-ESTIMATION-AUTOMATION` | Estimates story points with reasoning |
| **Bug Fix** | Tag: `KAI-BUGFIX-AUTOMATION` | Analyzes bug, creates fix branch + PR |
| **Dev Agent** | Tag: `KAI-DEV-AUTOMATION` | Full implementation — reads story, codes, creates PR |
| **QA Agent** | Tag: `KAI-QA-AUTOMATION` | Verifies component on AEM, captures screenshots |
| **Doc Agent** | Tag: `KAI-DOC-AUTOMATION` | Generates wiki documentation from completed story |

All work-item agents require the `KAI-TRIGGER` tag in addition to the agent-specific tag.

## How It Works (Simple Version)

```
Developer tags a ticket          Someone creates a PR
        |                                |
        v                                v
   ADO webhook fires              ADO build policy runs
        |                                |
        v                                v
   AWS Lambda routes              PR Review pipeline
   to the right pipeline          analyzes the diff
        |                                |
        v                                v
   ADO Pipeline runs              Posts review comments
   the AI agent                   on the PR
        |
        v
   Agent posts results
   as ADO comments (or creates a PR)
```

## Safety

- **Rate limits** — each agent has a daily cap (e.g., 50 PR reviews/day, 20 DoR checks/day)
- **Token budget** — monthly spending cap on AI API calls; alerts at 80%, degrades at 90%, halts at 100%
- **Policy gates** — agents can only do what their role allows (read-only agents can't push code)
- **Push policy** — code changes require 4 checks to pass before pushing (correct thread, unique match, lint passes, no injection detected)
- **Deduplication** — duplicate webhook events are silently dropped (DynamoDB with 1h TTL)

## Supported Tools

- **Claude Code** (CLI) — primary interface. Run `/dx-*` commands in terminal.
- **VS Code with GitHub Copilot** — same skills available as `@AgentName` in Copilot chat (e.g., `@DxPRReview`, `@DxCodeReview`).
